    <Content Sanitized="false" DataType="WikiText">
      <Data><![CDATA[==What to Do==

Compile production binaries with Automatic Reference Counting(ARC) enabled. ARC is only available on iOS 5 and higher.

==Why==

Using Automatic Reference Counting prevents use-after-free vulnerabilities.

==How==

To enable Automatic Reference Counting(ARC):

# **Use a compatible SDK.** Use iOS SDK 5.0 or higher to be able to use Automatic Reference Counting.
# **Launch XCode.** Open the XCode environment.
# **Enable Automatic Reference Counting.** Set the compiler option //Objective-C Automatic Reference Counting// to //yes//.

==Memory Management Guidelines==
* [[Compile Applications with Stack Cookies Enabled]]
* [[Do Not Reference Freed Objects]]
* [[Use Automatic Reference Counting]]

==Memory Management Checklists==
